President Obama spoke with Prime Minister David Cameron of the United Kingdom regarding the outcome of the Brexit referendum. The President assured Cameron that the special relationship between the US and UK, as well as the UK's membership in NATO, remain important to US foreign, security, and economic policy. Obama expressed regret at Cameron's decision to step aside and acknowledged him as a trusted partner and friend. The President also emphasized the EU's role in promoting stability, economic growth, and democratic values across Europe and beyond. Both leaders expressed confidence in the UK and EU's ability to negotiate a way forward that ensures financial stability, continued trade and investment, and mutual prosperity.